  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p>The accommodation choices in the Muotka Wilderness lodge include:</p>
<p><strong>Wilderness Rooms </strong>sleep two people and are located in the main reception building or in a separate building just a few steps away. All are tastefully decorated in a cosy Nordic style and have shower, WC and hairdryer. Beds can be made up as either a double or twins. These rooms are also available for sole occupancy.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Sauna Suites </strong>sleep two to four people and are located in a separate building. Spacious pine-clad one room suites with double bed, private sauna, and lounge area. Suites can accommodate 2 extra beds for children</p>
<p><strong>Panorama Log Cabins</strong> sleep two to four people in highly recommended spacious detached log cabins with double bed, private sauna, fireplace, lounge area, kitchenette and panoramic windows. These Cabins can accommodate 2 extra beds for children</p>
<p><strong>Aurora Cabins </strong>sleep two to four people. In a quiet location away from the main buildings these amazing one room cabins can be pre-booked for the first or last night during your stay. All have large panoramic north-facing semi-glass roofs with views of the night sky from your bed, private sauna, shower, WC, hairdryer, coffee/tea-maker. Some have a sofa bed that sleep two people. These rooms are available on request, as are single occupancy Aurora Cabins, please give our Reservations team a call to book.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Facilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Wi-Fi</li>
<li>Bathroom with shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer </li>
<li>Towels and linen</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
